                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="adamsmithinstitute_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a British organization formed in 1977 to give economic advice to the British government, foreign governments and other groups. It was named after the 18th-century <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/economist" title="economist definition"><span class="ndv">economist</span></a> <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/adam-smith#adam_smith_topg_1" title="Adam Smith definition"><span class="ndv">Adam Smith</span></a>, and shared many of his ideas (for example, about the importance of reducing the extent to which the state is involved in social and commercial affairs). It was associated particularly with the Conservative governments of the 1980s and 1990s in Britain.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
